<br>
I am in need of some of your wisdom.  My wizard is currently 34th level (about 20% from 35) and is the only alt that I currently play.  I do not 2-box (I have only 1 computer) and have only a single EQ account anyway, with a level 56 shaman as my main.  I am in a guild that I am very happy with, even though we aren't even NToV capable yet, let alone VT or the planes.  And *gasp* yes, I am a &quot;casual&quot; player, rarely playing for more than a couple hours a day.<br>
<br>
I thoroughly enjoy playing my wizzie, even to the point of having begun to neglect playing my shaman, and I may very well end up changing my main to the wizzie since my guild is VERY short on active wizzies (we have 2 main wizzies and a couple alts in the guild and the highest level main wizzie is all of 51-52).<br>
<br>
However, as a &quot;casual&quot; player, I am faced with a dilemma.  I don't quad kite.  It's something I've never tried, and something that I'm not sure entirely sure that I want to learn to do.  With my Shaman and Necromancer, I had no difficulty leveling into the mid-50's without ever needing to attempt a tactic as risky as quadding, and I've not seen any evidence that the other wizard I know who is around my level is leveling any faster than I am and he *IS* quadding spectres in the oasis while I single kite in the Overthere or Great Divide.<br>
<br>
Should I bite the bullet and start learning to quad? or are the supposed massive benefits of quadding another of those Everquest myths like class balance? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=614716">Thyrbit Firefrog</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garielhalliwell>Gariel Halliwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1385<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 6:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In need of Wizarding Advice..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Should I bite the bullet and start learning to quad? or are the supposed massive benefits of quadding another of those Everquest myths like class balance?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
I'd say learn to do it.  It's fun at least and I can't see how single kiting would be more effective.  I know I got a good bit more experience quadding the goranga as opposed to singling them.<br>
<br>
First, get a staff of temperate flux.  Then, go to something like Orc2 in Commons and snag 4 orcs.  4 orcs should not give you a problem and should let you get your technique down if you are too nervous to try it out on mobs your level.<br>
<br>
Sage Gariel Halliwell<br>
Arcanist of The Hand, Xev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 7:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In need of Wizarding Advice..</span><hr size=1> Bite it and savor it, Quad kiting is one of the best exp in the game. You might not notice it (especially when Circle of force is gimp vs mobs) but the skills you learn now will pay off, and exp is better than just marginally better.<br>
<br>
After you learn to kite like ^ said try the walruses in EW, nice quad material. or you could *gasp* try and get a group with guildies friends ect. Tho i like quadding becuase if i logged with buffs on i can just log in and play for 30 mins and not have to waste time on getting C3 finding a group getting it all ready and saying sorry i gotta go after we kill 3 mobs.<br>
<br>
 Its a good *casual* gamer tactic for getting exp if you find groups are had to come by (plz no hijacks on grouping)<br>
<br>
F3 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzitay>Azzitay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 7:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In need of Wizarding Advice..</span><hr size=1> Essentials<br>
<br>
Get Staff of Temperat Flux<br>
<br>
Get used to 3rd Person Point of view !! (3x F9 is my Favorite)<br>
<br>
Learn to run around in that Perspective !<br>
<br>
Grab 4 Mobs with staff (you can aggro while running with it) , run around em till they are almost in 1 spot .... snare em ...<br>
AE Nuke em till they are dead.<br>
<br>
Thats it ... KEI and other Buffs help a LOT.<br>
If you learned it with Orcs ... grab some HP buff along with a KEI and maybe get a Skin up ...<br>
ALL Wizards get caught by their Quads now and then ... we get lazy , have a lag Spike ... whatever.<br>
<br>
But all those quads u do well will compensate the Exp loss =)<br>
<br>
And if you are not in mood for Quadding you can Tradeskill ...<br>
The exp is that good that you can actually take some time for it =)<br>
Have fun =) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Azzitay Flammenpfad, Ratsmitglied <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.der-schatten.com" target="top">Der Schatten</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->,</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Sage Chimaeron Emrys, Member of Wind of Tranquility</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gebbly>Gebbly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 298<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 7:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Read Bicrius' guide...</span><hr size=1> I only recently got the hang of quadding and I have to say the xp just rolls in now. As a casual player myself I used to spend a night getting a gold bubble. Now I can spend a night getting almost a whole level.<br>
There were the 2 or 3 deaths whilst I was getting the hang of it but after that its sorted.<br>
<br>
Heres a good starter manual:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm28.showMessage?topicID=2.topic">pub140.ezboard.com/fgraff...ID=2.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
A few tips :<br>
watch carefully for mobs resisting your BoF. This can make controlling the quad difficult. Learn which mobs have higher resists. For example if quadding ulthorks although hunters and warriors were both dark blue to me the warriors resisted far more. So at first I stayed away from warriors whilst learning.<br>
<br>
If things start to go pear-shaped be prepared to get out of there earlier than you would if you were single pulling. (4 dark blue mobs can make mincemeat of you very quickly)<br>
<br>
and be sure to have a SoW! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quineloe>Quineloe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1788<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 7:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Read Bicrius' guide...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Get used to 3rd Person Point of view<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
