mind that the freaking named drake is VERY annoying and chalk two of my deaths up to him. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.questorsmoy.com/eqmemberinfopages/storyrenia/reniasig3.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quikpick>Quikpick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 651<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 1:22 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> The key to quading in 3rd person view is to setup your cameras prior to the quad. Each place you quad in, the camera may be blocked via a wall, hill, etc. Adjust them to each location and quading in 3rd person becomes easier. I would also get a timer mod to tell you when snare is about to wear off. <p><p><P><p align="center"><strong><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55973"><font color="#00CC00">Sage Quikpick Emberlore</a></font><BR><font color="#999999">Sorceress of Chronology</font></strong><BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fitzroyy>Fitzroyy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/03 1:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> I also fall under the &quot;casual player&quot; heading and from your level, I mostly single kited.  I did however learn to quad, and once I hit 40 have been doing it almost exclusively.  Nothing like getting an orange bar in about one hour of play.  Mind you that includes some decent (not great) equipment and a KEI.  <br>
<br>
Haven't gone in for the hp buffs.  If I mess up that bad, they usually don't slow down my death that much, and I tend to be more cocky while using them.  A dangerous habit.  <br>
<br>
For your level, you can start exp quad on gnolls in South Karana.  They're sort of slow and give decent exp and loot.  If you can find them open of course, but that has been more likely recently.<br>
<br>
